Saluda  was first listed as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]].<ref name=2010CensusVA/>

The population stated in the [[United States Census, 2010|2010 Census]] was 769.<ref>[http://mcdc.missouri.edu/webrepts/pl94trends/Virginia_stplace2.html Virginia Trend Report 2: State and Complete Places (Sub-state 2010 Census Data).] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.today/20120711160933/http://mcdc.missouri.edu/webrepts/pl94trends/Virginia_stplace2.html|date=2012-07-11}} Missouri Census Data Center. Accessed 2011-06-08.</ref> As of the [[2020 United States census|2020 Census]], the population was 627. According to the 2020 Census, Saluda has a 55.6% [[employment rate]], 228 total houses with 125 belonging to families, and a [[Median income|medium income]] of $115,221 with a 10.7% [[poverty rate]]. Out of the population, 451 are white, 134 are black, 28 are mixed race, 1 is Asian, 1 is Native American, and 12 are other.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Saluda CDP, Virginia |url=https://data.census.gov/profile/Saluda_CDP,_Virginia?g=160XX00US5170112 |access-date=2024-05-26 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

